The White House has announced the creation of a Global Technology and Innovation Fund to support technological development in Muslim-majority countries. The fund, which is being launched by the Overseas Private Investment Corporation, will facilitate private sector investments in technology in OPIC-eligible countries in Asia, the Middle East, and Africa. The fund will provide financing of $25 million to $150 million for selected projects. The goal of the fund is to promote economic opportunity and job creation in Muslim-majority countries. Sectors of interest for prospective funds include technology, education, telecom, media, business services, financial technology, and clean-tech. More information about the fund can be found at http://www.opic.gov/investment-funds/calls-for-proposals/global-technology-innovation-fund/.